comment: Offset: -1.4 •600µL ink were employed (1:1 ratio - liposuctate:hydrogel) -> it is important to thoroughly mix before pipeting & pipet the ink right in the middle of the print head, avoid bubbles, cut the end of the pipet tip to be able to pipet LS •Individual constructs are discernable, but connected with each other through liposuctate tissue --> need to be cautiously seperated
next steps: •Print head & VAT are cleaned  •Exposure time is increased to 30s (25s is simply overwritten - material settings itself are not changed) to increase the resolution of resulting cylinders

comment: Offset: -1.4 •600µL ink were employed •Resolution seems to have increased, all further printing is conducted with 30s  •Individual constructs need to be separated •Discs look very thin --> hard to handle, less "substance"
next steps: •Print head & VAT are cleaned  •New offset: -0.9 to reach 1.5 mm construct height instead of 1 mm (STL file remains the same, meaining: accounting for just 1mm)

comment: Offset: -0.9 •LS processed by 3-way stop cock •1mL in (1:1 ratio) is used as construct height is increased by 1/2 •Individual constructs are separated with spatula •Inhomogenous distribution of hydrogel and LS: some discs show more LS ratio, others more hydrogel
next steps: •Residual ink is covered by plate lid to protect against evaporation, decreasing temperature and sticky residuals on VAT •Constructs are washed with warm PBS and gently removed with a spatula (wet it with PBS before to simplify removal) •Print head is cleaned  •Residual ink is removed as much as possible avoiding scrathing of the VAT, but no cleaning of VAT necessary as 2 print runs with identical ink are conducted and only one layer is exposed (thereby minimizing the risk of disruptive sticky remains on VAT)

comment: Offset: -0.9 •LS processed by 3-way stop cock •1mL in (1:1 ratio) is used •Individual constructs are separated with spatula •Inhomogenous distribution of hydrogel and LS
next steps: •Print head & VAT are cleaned  •Out of the 18, 16 constructs are selected and placed in DMEM high glucose+10%FBS+1%P/S (2304XYMB)  •Printing with next condition is initiated
